        "content": "<p>personally i'd try to avoid this kind of inductive... For example, you might be happier using <code>inductive Bar where | foo n : Foo | bar n : Foo</code>, to then work with the subtype <code>Foo x := {b : Bar| F b.out = x}</code>. When you need to rewrite , use a <code>cast</code> function, such that the rewrites are cleaner and part of the object, as well as in a way that the kernel gets to forget when trying to match on the actual value.</p>",
        "id": 497199018,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1738444614
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for a concrete usecase of this pattern, check out <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=List.Vector#doc\">docs#List.Vector</a></p>",
        "id": 497199085,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1738444682
